Jonas says the country's growth is trapped and must be unlocked through various interventions - one of them being political stability. JOHANNESBURG - Former deputy finance minister Mcebisi Jonas has urged the business sector to call out government on the mixed signals it sends out on economic policies which create uncertainty.Jonas says the country's growth is trapped and must be unlocked through various interventions - one of them being political stability.Mcebisi Jonas says the government must get its house in order regarding what it plans around certain economic policies. Mixed signals on economic policy, sometimes, this morning you wake up talking about radical economic transformation, tomorrow you re talking about intrusive growth. He says one of the contributing factors is populist statements by politicians and economic illiteracy.Jonas says he hopes there will be more stability following the ANC's elective conference in December this year.(Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)